header: Test vectors of type Keywrap are intended for tests
checking the wrapping and unwrapping of key material.

CounterOverflow.description: The test vector contains a value that is long enough so that the round counter becames larger than 256.

EmptyKey.description: An empty key cannot be wrapped. Incorrectly wrapping an empty key may result in key independent result. Incorrectly unwrapping an empty key may allow to circumvent authentication.

InvalidWrappingSize.description: The size of the wrapped key is invalid

ModifiedIv.description: The test vector contains a ciphertext that was obtained with an incorrect IV. Unwrapping should verify that the IV is valid and hence reject this test vector.

Normal.description: The test vector contains a pseudorandomly generated, valid test case. Implementations are expected to pass this test.

ShortKey.description: NIST SP 800-38F does not define the wrapping of 8 byte keys. RFC 3394 Section 2 on the other hand specifies that 8 byte keys are wrapped by directly encrypting one block with AES.

WrongDataSize.description: KW cannot be used to wrap a key that is not a multiple of 8 bytes. Inputs of such sizes should be rejected.
